SFH-environment correlation.

Figure: Exploring the correlation between the star formation histories (SFHs) of individual galaxies and their environments in the CANDELS/GOODS-S field.

For this exercise, we use a small subset of bright (F160w<24 mags) galaxies at z~1. (Riverside sample: Pacifici et al. 2019, in prep.)

Left: The density contrast at z~1 estimated using an adaptive kernel smoothing method (Charlab et al. 2019, in prep.) used to quantify the effects of environment.

Right: Galaxies in our sample at z~1. The sizes of the circles are proportional to each galaxy's stellar mass, and their color is proportional to their environment, with green (purple) colors tracing dense (field) environments.

Hovering over individual galaxies will show their SFHs, reconstructed using the Dense Basis SED fitting method (Iyer et al. 2019, submitted to ApJ).

Since it might be difficult to examine individual galaxies in high density regions, users can use the box zoom tool to study them in more detail.

The plot can be brought back to its original state by presing the reset button.
